<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496663>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Thesium fragile: (A) growth habit and coastal sand substrate of the plant, (B) closer view of the fruiting female plants, (C) indeterminate flowering shoot with scale-like leaves subtending branchlets, bracts and bracteoles, (D) flowering shoot showing tetramerous flower and stamens in male plant, (E) female shoot borne with truncate whitish fruit capped with yellowish long persistent perianth remnants.Photographs:Daniel Zhigila." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496663/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

